caption.text:
On Friday the 6th join us for a discussion with Michael Hardt on the Global War Regime. Doors at 6:30pm, event at 7pm. 414 Broadway, 3rd Floor.

We're told that the wars that ravage the globe present us with few options - either embrace nation-state actors in their conflicts, or to return to a struggle for national liberation. In a series of texts written with Sandro Mezzadra, Michael Hardt has recently argued for a new internationalist struggle against the global war regime - taking inspiration from the many ongoing transnational struggles around the globe. For Hardt and Mezzadra the global war regime is both a perpetual manipulation of capitalist circulation, as well as a system of domestic and international governance. This frame gives Hardt the basis for an alternative to the tired and outdated formulas of campist nationalisms. Join us this Friday to discuss these questions, as we witness daily the perpetual civil war in American life.

READINGS: 
--"A Global War Regime" - Michael Hardt & Sandro Mezzadra, 2024: https://newleftreview.org/sidecar/posts/a-global-war-regime
--"The Coming Post-Hegemonic World" - Michael Hardt & Sandro Mezzadra, 2025: https://www.versobooks.com/blogs/news/the-coming-post-hegemonic-world
--"Capital and the Global War Regime" - Michael Hardt & Sandro Mezzadra, 2025: https://portolan-journal.org/?post=capital-and-the-global-war-regime

Michael Hardt teaches political theory in the Literature Program at Duke University. He is co-author, with Antonio Negri, of the Empire trilogy and, most recently, Assembly. He is co-director with Sandro Mezzadra of The Social Movements Lab.

caption.text:
@filmores.gentlemens.club was the first adult entertainment club I ever went to. I chose Filmores because I always loved the anticipation of passing by the building on the Dundas streetcar whenever I was heading out the east end and seeing how the sign had changed since the last time. 

I went in wondering if a friend I knew was working that night and if I‚Äôd run into them. The DJ was hounding the patrons in the front row of the stage for not tipping the dancers and saying, ‚ÄúWhat is this National Geographic, there‚Äôs a bunch of hyenas in the crowd tonight‚Äù. 

I remember who gave me my first lap dance. It was my birthday. My friends scrounged up some cash for me and another friend to go for a dance. I picked out a dancer covered in tattoos. All I remember was her saying, ‚ÄúYou can touch me anywhere but my pussy‚Äù. The rest went by quickly.

It‚Äôs not just Filmores, it‚Äôs that Toronto is consistently losing places that gives the city character and charm. People in my life know how much I love this city yet it is increasingly harder and harder to stay living as a working class artist. 

I love learning about the history of the city‚Äôs taboo sexual underworld and collecting items from this past. Even moreso now that @kiwithestripp3r has been in my personal life. 

The closing of Filmores is a big sad moment for many, grateful to have some cherished memories of the club while it was around.

PS, this poster is actually addressed to ‚ÄúDavid‚Äù, has been in my collection for a couple of years now and is current l not for sale.

caption.text:
Power outage update (2/1, 9 PM):

I‚Äôm deeply concerned by what residents are experiencing right now. While operations are being described as ‚Äúongoing,‚Äù neighbors are reporting no Con Edison staff on site and a loss of power following generator installation. That gap between what‚Äôs being said and what‚Äôs happening on the ground is unacceptable.

We need clear answers: when will the two temporary generators be fully operational and restoring power to all impacted residents? Which addresses remain without service? And what immediate support is available for non-NYCHA residents who are currently without heat and power while repairs continue? We are grateful to know the NYCHA buildings have full temporary power.

With freezing temperatures and real risks to families, children, seniors, and buildings, I am demanding more frequent and transparent updates from both NYC Emergency Management and Con Edison ahead of the Monday 2/2, 9 AM elected‚Äô follow-up. Our community deserves better.

If you‚Äôre impacted, please file a claim with Con Edison and notify my office so we can escalate cases and hold them accountable. Send to District39@council.nyc.gov.

user.full_name: Tatjana  *  G r e e n
Tatjana  *  G r e e n

caption.text:
End of January. Simple and classic dishes. Roasted duck leg with port wine sauce, la rattle potatoes, foie gras and preserved peach from autumn, cooked first low and slow, then finished during service in butter with sage. Foie gras on toast, sauteed fennel with truffles, pear jam. Pretty slices of truffle. 
Cat with her spider toy. Cabbage and smiles, hands covered in blood and salt. 
.
